23/02/2010
THE HAGUE, The Netherlands -- UN war crimes tribunal President Patrick Robinson has approved a request by former Bosnian Serb leader Radovan Karadzic for additional funding for his legal team, the court announced on Monday (February 22nd). According to the decision, the tribunal will pay eight members of Karadzic's team before the trial begins on March 1st and five more after it starts. Karadzic asked the tribunal on February 1st to delay resumption of his trial, claiming he needed more time to prepare and more money for his advisers. (Tanjug, Beta, B92 - 22/02/10)
